name: NutritionAnthropometricMeasurePanelLOINC
title: Nutrition Anthropometric Measure Panel LOINC
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Anthropometric non invasive measurements are used as part of a nutrition assessment by a nutrition professional.),(Data Element Scope: Anthropometric data includes height, weight, body mass index (BMI), growth pattern indices/percentiles, weight history, hand grip strength, and other indices that are part of a nutrition assessment conducted by a nutritionist.),(Inclusion Criteria: Any measurements which are evidence based indicators of nutrition status or related condition.),(Exclusion Criteria: N/A)
